premise_source_doc_sentence: `` Erskine Henry Bronson and Walter Goodman Bronson carried on the family business after the death of their father in 1899 , followed by Frederick Erskine Bronson after the death of Walter Goodman Bronson in 1932 .
The Harris , Bronson and Coleman  (  later Harris and Bronson  )  company mainly supplied markets in the northeastern United States .
Bronson Avenue took its name from Ottawa businessman and politician  (  Ontario MLA  )  Erskine Henry Bronson .
He platted the town in 1831 and named it the village of Bronson  (  not to be confused with the much smaller Bronson , Michigan about 50 miles  (  80 km  )  to the south-southeast  )  .
The village of Bronson was renamed Kalamazoo in 1836  (  due in part to an incident resulting in Bronson 's being fined for stealing a cherry tree  )  .
